format date & time values as stirngs

strftime([format [, timestamp[, utc-flag]]])
format: string which specifies the foramt of o/p string.
it contains conversion specifiers that are replaced by correspoding date & time values.
%Y replace year, %m replace month, %d replace date.
If format is omitted then %c is used as default.

timestamp: optional integer value that represents the time to be formatted. on omitting current time is ued.

utc-flag: optional boolean vlaue that indicates whether to use UTC insted of the local time. it set then it is used.

